00:35:54.000 --> 00:36:00.880
grow, but I think probably the
fact of loss is always there

00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:03.360
with the beautiful
things that are growing.

00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:07.450
You know, I think it's probably
actually the truth, you know.

00:36:07.450 --> 00:36:10.050
Even the most abundant
and ebullient sort

00:36:10.050 --> 00:36:18.930
of exaltative poem has loss
around it, touching it.

00:36:18.930 --> 00:36:20.230
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: It's
honest, if it's honest.

00:36:20.230 --> 00:36:22.770
&gt;&gt; Ross Gay: Yeah, if it's
honest, yeah totally, yeah.

