01:05:47.710 --> 01:05:49.010
&gt;&gt; Ross Gay: Yeah.

01:05:49.010 --> 01:05:54.260
It's called Wedding Poem, yeah
for my friends Keith and Jen.

01:05:54.260 --> 01:05:59.610
Friends, I am here to modestly
report seeing in an orchard

01:05:59.610 --> 01:06:05.460
in my town a gold finch kissing
a sun flower again and again,

01:06:05.460 --> 01:06:09.840
dangling upside down by its
tiny claws, steadying itself

01:06:09.840 --> 01:06:12.530
by snapping open
like an old tiny fan,

01:06:12.530 --> 01:06:15.500
its wings, again, and again.

01:06:15.500 --> 01:06:19.020
Until swooning it tumbled
off and swooped back

01:06:19.020 --> 01:06:21.170
to the very same perch,

01:06:21.170 --> 01:06:24.620
where the sunflower curled
its giant swirling of seeds

01:06:24.620 --> 01:06:26.510
around the bird and leaned back

01:06:26.510 --> 01:06:31.400
to admire the soft wind
nudging the bird's plumage.

01:06:31.400 --> 01:06:33.100
And friends, I could
see the points

01:06:33.100 --> 01:06:37.110
on the flower's stately
crown soften and curl inward

01:06:37.110 --> 01:06:40.580
as it almost indiscernibly
lifted the food of its body

01:06:40.580 --> 01:06:43.820
to the bird's nuzzling mouth,
whose fervor I could hear

01:06:43.820 --> 01:06:47.940
from oh 20 or so feet away
and see from the tiny hulls

01:06:47.940 --> 01:06:51.430
that sailed form their good
racket, which good racket,

01:06:51.430 --> 01:06:55.290
I have to say, was
making me blush and rock

01:06:55.290 --> 01:06:58.920
up on my tippy toes and
just barely purse my lips

01:06:58.920 --> 01:07:04.330
with what I realize now
was being simply glad,

01:07:04.330 --> 01:07:09.510
which such love, if we
let it, makes us feel.

